Status: DISCARD  (Training residual mean doesn't generalise — slight overfit)

================================================================================
EXP 6 — Polynomial & log lag features + lower regularisation
================================================================================
Change  : Added log_lag1, log_lag52, lag1_sq (scaled), lag1×lag52 interaction,
          and trend_ratio (roll4/roll26). Reduced reg_alpha 0.1→0.05,
          reg_lambda 0.5→0.3.
Insight : Polynomial features allow the model to capture non-linear
          relationships between lag values (e.g. very high lag_1 predicts
          even higher relative uplift on holiday weeks).

---
r2:      0.999862   (+0.000088 vs baseline)
mae:     158.44
rmse:    371.03
wmae:    238.99      (-116.98 vs baseline)
mape:    0.4488
seconds: 421.4
---
Status: KEEP ✓

================================================================================
EXP 7 — 4-model blend: added LGB3 with L2 (RMSE) objective
================================================================================
Change  : Added a 4th LightGBM model with objective=regression_l2 (optimises
          RMSE rather than MAE). This model is more sensitive to large
          prediction errors, complementing the L1 models.
Insight : L1 and L2 objectives minimise different loss functions. L2 is more
          aggressive on outlier weeks (holiday spikes), while L1 is robust.
          Their blend reduces both types of error.

---
r2:      0.999895   (+0.000121 vs baseline)
mae:     151.23
rmse:    320.88
wmae:    202.47      (-153.50 vs baseline)
mape:    0.4280
seconds: 549.1
---
Status: KEEP ✓

================================================================================
EXP 8 — 5-model blend: added LGB4 with Huber loss + DART boosting
================================================================================
Change  : Added 5th model: LightGBM with Huber loss (alpha=0.9) and DART
          boosting (dropout additive regression trees). DART provides
          regularisation via random tree dropout. scipy Nelder-Mead blend.
Note    : DART is slow (no early stopping) — took ~15 min.

---
r2:      0.999902   (+0.000128 vs baseline)
mae:     155.20
rmse:    340.92
wmae:    201.11      (-154.86 vs baseline)
mape:    0.4836
seconds: 905.8
---
Status: KEEP ✓

================================================================================
EXP 9 — Replace DART with naive EWM predictor in 6-way blend (DISCARDED)
================================================================================
Hypothesis: A simple weighted lag average (0.5×lag1 + 0.25×lag2 + ...) is a
            strong standalone predictor that adds diversity to the ensemble.
Note    : Used fast Huber-LGB4 instead of slow DART.

---
r2:      0.999901
wmae:    201.99
seconds: 1161.7
---
Status: DISCARD  (Naive predictor and GOSS-Huber combo even slower, no gain)

================================================================================
EXP 10 — Replace DART with holiday-specific sub-model  ★ BEST ★
================================================================================
Change  : Replaced slow Huber-DART with a dedicated LightGBM trained
          exclusively on holiday weeks (hol_tr subset). For holiday validation
          weeks, the holiday model's predictions replace the generic model's.
          For non-holiday weeks, LGB1 predictions are used.
Insight : Holiday demand patterns are structurally different from regular
          weeks. A model trained only on holiday data learns store-level
          holiday uplift patterns that a general model averages out.

---
r2:      0.999902   (+0.000128 vs baseline)
mae:     148.71
rmse:    316.25
wmae:    197.48      (-158.49 vs baseline)   ← NEW BEST WMAE
mape:    0.4203
seconds: 686.2
---
Status: KEEP ✓  (Same R², better WMAE, 25% faster than Exp8)

